scoringPlays.text: Karan Higdon 2 Yd Run (Quinn Nordin Kick)
Kendric Pryor 33 Yd Run (Rafael Gaglianone Kick)
Shea Patterson 7 Yd Run (Shea Patterson Pass to Nico Collins for Two-Point Conversion)
Lavert Hill 21 Yd Interception Return (Quinn Nordin Kick)
Dylan McCaffrey 44 Yd Run (Quinn Nordin Kick)
A.J. Taylor 3 Yd pass from Alex Hornibrook (Two-Point Pass Conversion Failed)

videos.description: Shea Patterson keeps it himself and charges down the sideline, getting all the way to the 5-yard line to set up Michigan's first touchdown.
videos.headline: Patterson breaks off 81-yard run

videos.description: Karan Higdon gets through a hole and finds the end zone to give Michigan a 7-0 lead over Wisconsin.
videos.headline: Michigan strikes first with 2-yard TD run

videos.description: WR Kendric Pryor takes the jet sweep and gets to the outside, showing off his speed and tying the game at 7-7.
videos.headline: Wisconsin answers with 33-yard TD run

videos.description: David Long tips Alex Hornibrook's pass, and Josh Metellus comes down with the interception to set up a Wolverine's field goal.
videos.headline: Michigan picks off Hornibrook

videos.description: Shea Patterson reaches across the goal line for a TD, then connects with Nico Collins for the 2-point conversion, extending Michigan's lead to 21-7.
videos.headline: Patterson fakes out defense for 7-yard TD run

videos.description: Lavert Hill anticipates Alex Hornibrook's pass and returns it to the house, growing the Wolverines' 4th quarter lead to 31-7.
videos.headline: Michigan blows it open with pick-6

videos.description: Backup QB Dylan McCaffrey finds and lane and outruns the defense down the sideline, giving Michigan a 38-7 lead over Wisconsin.
videos.headline: Wolverines pour it on with 44-yard QB run

videos.description: A visibly excited Chase Winovich reflects on the Wolverines' convincing win over the Badgers, explaining what it means to get a win in primetime.
videos.headline: Winovich: 'We're a hungry team'

videos.description: Chase Winovich shows some love to Shea Patterson, who discusses his big day on the ground and the Wolverines' winning mindset.
videos.headline: Winovich and Patterson all smiles after win

videos.description: Shea Patterson's big game, 124 yards passing and 105 yards on the ground for one score, propels Michigan to a 38-13 win over Wisconsin.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Michigan with statement W over Wisconsin) 2018/10/13 ESHEET SOTFULL

videos.headline: Michigan with statement W over Wisconsin

videos.description: It was Michigan's quarterback who got its ground game rolling, as Shea Patterson totaled 90 rush yards and a score in a statement win.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Patterson runs wild on Wisconsin) 2018/10/13 ESHEET ENHL

videos.headline: Patterson runs wild on Wisconsin
